cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with visual social relationship recognition using images. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a computational model for understanding social relationships from visual data. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes an Adaptive Focal Loss for more effective learning. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing images and social relationships in a multimedia context. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also relevant as the paper aims to build intelligent machines that can better interact with humans in a social environment.
